duck: The sport of Mounted orienteering (Techniques de Randonnée Équestre de Compétition).
Texas Real Estate Commission, the state agency that governs real estate practices in Texas.
Text REtrieval Conference, an on-going series of workshops co-sponsored by the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) and the U.S. Department of Defense.
T-cell receptor excision circles - T-cell receptor excision circles (TRECs) are small circles of DNA created in T-cells during their passage through the thymus as they rearrange their TCR genes.
Toronto Renewable Energy Co-operative - creators of the WindShare wind power co-operative in Toronto, Canada

The Trans-Mediterranean Renewable Energy Cooperation is an initiative, in the field of renewable forms of energy, of The Club of Rome, the Hamburg Climate Protection Foundation and the National Energy Research Center of Jordan (NERC).

wiki.text:
'TREC' may refer to:
* Techniques de Randonnée Équestre de Compétition or Trec, an equestrian
  discipline
* Text REtrieval Conference, an on-going series of workshops co-sponsored by the
  National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) and the U.S. Department
  of Defense.
* Texas Real Estate Commission, the state agency that governs real estate
  practices in Texas.
* The Trans-Mediterranean Renewable Energy Cooperation is an initiative, in
  the field of renewable forms of energy, of The Club of Rome, the Hamburg
  Climate Protection Foundation and the National Energy Research Center of
  Jordan (NERC).
* Toronto Renewable Energy Co-operative - creators of the WindShare wind power
  co-operative in Toronto, Canada
* T-cell receptor excision circles
